04:20.219 --> 04:23.256
DAVIS: (LAUGHING) I can do this for you.

04:24.807 --> 04:27.173
I can't pay you.

04:27.268 --> 04:30.886
I'm just getting
cost covered as it is. I can't afford you.

04:30.980 --> 04:32.516
Not for pay.

04:33.524 --> 04:35.389
Not for pay?

04:35.484 --> 04:39.068
Why would you do it without getting paid?

04:39.155 --> 04:43.945
Because I'm a giver.
I give, and I give, and I give.

04:45.661 --> 04:47.367
Come on, face the facts.

04:47.455 --> 04:50.447
Look, I've lived almost half my life,

04:50.583 --> 04:53.575
if I'm honest, wasting a quarter of it.

04:53.669 --> 04:54.704
What do I have to show, huh?

04:55.546 --> 05:00.131
I'm a part-time diskjockey,
a part-time musician,

05:00.217 --> 05:03.254
a part-time lover of extraordinary women

05:03.345 --> 05:05.802
that nonetheless work 80 hours a week

05:05.890 --> 05:08.302
and are therefore willing to settle.

05:08.392 --> 05:11.634
I'm not settling. I mean,
not any more than you are.

05:11.729 --> 05:17.144
(SIGHS) I'm just saying,
it's time for me to go full-time in life.

05:17.234 --> 05:18.815
You're scaring me, Davis.

05:18.903 --> 05:21.315
I mean, where's the Davis McAlary who said,

05:21.405 --> 05:24.238
"Any job on which
you can't be seen with a |itjoint

05:24.325 --> 05:26.031
"is a job not worthy of consideration?"

05:26.118 --> 05:29.906
When I was a child, I spoke as a child.

05:30.748 --> 05:32.613
Janette? Hmm?

05:33.417 --> 05:34.702
Let me do this.

05:35.920 --> 05:37.876
All right, Davis.

05:39.924 --> 05:42.916
I need you there at 5:30.

05:43.010 --> 05:45.001
Don't be late.

05:56.232 --> 05:57.597
(PHONE RINGING)

05:58.150 --> 05:59.390
Yes, sir.

05:59.485 --> 06:01.567
You can go in, Lieutenant.

06:10.287 --> 06:12.118
What did you want to see me for, Chief?

06:12.248 --> 06:14.034
Your transfer, it's been approved.

06:15.417 --> 06:16.577
To where?

06:16.710 --> 06:17.825
Back to the Eighth as requested.

06:17.920 --> 06:19.535
Effective after the holiday.

06:21.507 --> 06:23.623
You'll also be happy to
know that I've been asked by the Chief

06:23.717 --> 06:26.129
to oversee an internal initiative aimed

06:26.303 --> 06:28.715
at reducing departmental corruption.

06:28.806 --> 06:31.548
An internal initiative?

06:31.642 --> 06:35.510
Policing ourselves under
your discerning eye, huh, Chief?

06:36.897 --> 06:37.886
Too late.

06:37.982 --> 06:39.188
What?

06:39.316 --> 06:40.522
Too little too late.

06:40.609 --> 06:45.319
I'm testifying, Deputy. Tomorrow, in fact.

06:54.832 --> 06:58.450
LAWYER: Here, here,
and here. I need a full signature right there.

07:01.005 --> 07:02.541
It's gonna be quite a medical center.

07:02.673 --> 07:04.254
With a biotech component.

07:04.341 --> 07:06.457
Something to rival the Houston Complex,

07:06.594 --> 07:08.710
thanks to planning and patience.

07:08.804 --> 07:10.669
Well, here's to planning and patience.

07:11.599 --> 07:13.009
LAWYER: Okay, your last copies.

07:13.100 --> 07:16.092
Gonna go here and here.
Initial on the corner of each page.

07:16.186 --> 07:18.973
Now that we're unburdening
you of all this New Orleans real estate,

07:19.064 --> 07:22.147
I'm guessing that
the last order of business for Nelson Hidalgo

07:22.234 --> 07:24.270
is to see the Jazz Center get the green light.

07:24.361 --> 07:27.444
That would frost the cake, wouldn't it?

07:27.531 --> 07:28.862
-Thank you.
-Where's that project now?

07:28.949 --> 07:31.611
A big meeting
at the Times-Pic after Mardi Gras.

07:31.702 --> 07:33.363
Irvin Mayfield and our development team

07:33.537 --> 07:35.118
are presenting to the editorial board there.

07:35.205 --> 07:36.866
High hopes?

07:37.041 --> 07:38.702
Don't know. Could be rocky.

07:39.668 --> 07:41.124
You gonna be there at the Times-Pic?

07:41.754 --> 07:44.370
Too much profile for me.

07:44.465 --> 07:46.205
When was your flight back to Galveston?

07:46.884 --> 07:48.590
I know you've got your hands full there.

07:48.677 --> 07:50.713
I'm out this afternoon, but I can fly back,

07:50.804 --> 07:52.544
be your eyes and ears
if you need me in the room.

07:52.723 --> 07:54.259
Oh, good man.

07:54.350 --> 07:56.807
Mr. Hidalgo? Your payout.

07:56.894 --> 07:58.259
(WHISTLES SOFTLY)

08:02.900 --> 08:04.561
(MARCHING BAND PLAYING)

08:22.920 --> 08:24.251
(BLOWING WHISTLE)

08:25.214 --> 08:29.332
All right. That's not bad.
Take a little breather. I'll be right back.

08:30.344 --> 08:31.459
(LaDONNA LAUGHS)

08:31.553 --> 08:32.542
LaDonna.

08:32.638 --> 08:34.094
Whoa!

08:34.848 --> 08:36.964
I am impressed.

08:37.059 --> 08:38.515
You were just driving by or...

08:38.644 --> 08:40.134
No, I was in the neighborhood.

08:40.229 --> 08:41.514
So, you marching on Mardi Gras day?

08:41.647 --> 08:42.932
Oh, not this year.

08:43.023 --> 08:45.685
We're doing Lundi Gras
Monday afternoon by the river.

08:45.776 --> 08:47.607
You know, Zulu Fest.

08:47.695 --> 08:51.654
So, you're not busy on Mardi Gras day.

08:51.740 --> 08:53.196
I didn't say that.

08:53.283 --> 08:54.443
(BOTH LAUGHING)

08:54.785 --> 08:57.151
Alcide is riding in the truck parade.

08:57.246 --> 08:59.828
I'll be there. Yeah.

09:00.874 --> 09:02.785
-I guess I should get back...
-Hey.

09:04.128 --> 09:05.868
I really need to talk to you.

09:07.172 --> 09:10.209
All right. I'm done in a half an hour.

09:10.718 --> 09:12.049
Okay.

09:12.261 --> 09:13.797
(PLAYING SOFT MUSIC)

09:16.640 --> 09:18.847
(UPBEAT BAND RECORDING PLAYING)

09:28.318 --> 09:29.899
(BAND RECORDING INAUDIBLE)

09:36.577 --> 09:38.283
(BAND RECORDING PLAYING)

09:38.871 --> 09:42.284
How about that one?
It's close enough for government work, right?

09:42.374 --> 09:45.332
Kidding. That was a joke.
That was beautiful, Annie.

09:45.419 --> 09:46.659
I got a better one in me.

09:47.421 --> 09:49.878
Okay, we can roll
when you're ready. Take eight.

09:49.965 --> 09:53.924
You know, we can
get the solo perfect, and we will,

09:54.011 --> 09:56.172
but this song isn't me, Marvin.

09:56.263 --> 09:57.469
You trust me, Annie.

09:57.556 --> 10:00.389
Steve wrote itjust for you. Custom delivery.

10:00.476 --> 10:01.807
It's a little generic, isn't it?

10:01.894 --> 10:03.475
Are you sure we don't have it 'cause Alison

10:03.604 --> 10:05.140
or Emmylou threw it back on the pile?

10:05.647 --> 10:07.729
You've got something to bring to it.

10:07.858 --> 10:09.940
You'll see when we go to the vocals.

10:10.027 --> 10:11.983
ADAM: Okay, take eight. Rolling.

10:12.446 --> 10:14.357
(BAND RECORDING PLAYING
FAINTLY ON HEADPHONES)

10:20.954 --> 10:23.821
Why now? They're not
getting along with Larry?

10:23.916 --> 10:26.874
No, they're getting along with Larry fine.

10:27.961 --> 10:31.249
They're just acting out.

10:34.051 --> 10:36.667
Alcide, Randall?

10:36.762 --> 10:39.378
Alcide's grades are
slipping. He's gonna be a senior next year.

10:39.473 --> 10:41.680
This is not the time.

10:42.810 --> 10:47.179
And, Antoine, Randall got into a fight.

10:48.816 --> 10:50.602
-Our Randall?
-Yes.

10:51.151 --> 10:52.391
(SIGHS)

10:53.320 --> 10:56.232
Larry's done more than his fair share.

10:56.323 --> 10:58.188
I moved out of the Residence Inn.

10:58.325 --> 11:00.190
I'm staying in the apartment above the bar

11:00.285 --> 11:03.243
so I can save money
so I can get a place for me and the boys.

11:04.331 --> 11:07.243
But that's not gonna happen until the fall.

11:08.293 --> 11:10.545
So in the meantime...

11:15.968 --> 11:18.380
I'll talk to Desiree.

11:20.931 --> 11:24.014
What's so amazing
is they just don't seem to care what we write.

11:24.101 --> 11:26.934
Your piece in The Nation
ran, and you could almost hear them yawn.

11:27.688 --> 11:29.019
BRENDAN: That's the attitude around here.

11:29.106 --> 11:31.688
No matter what we write,
they figure they'll just ride it out.

11:31.775 --> 11:34.357
Well, you give all of these deaths

11:34.486 --> 11:37.023
all of this space, a five-part series.

11:37.114 --> 11:38.729
They can't ignore that, right?

11:39.783 --> 11:41.614
What? (LAUGHS) You guys.

11:42.369 --> 11:45.361
Where's the file on the one
near the Convention Center?

11:45.455 --> 11:47.241
What's-his-name? Yep.

11:47.624 --> 11:49.125
Dude, it's getting late here.

11:49.626 --> 11:51.241
It's the afternoon, Brendan.

11:51.336 --> 11:52.872
WOMAN: On the Thursday before Mardi Gras.

11:52.963 --> 11:54.203
-Ah.
-Muses rolls tonight.

11:54.298 --> 11:56.163
Some of us have to work Mardi Gras coverage.

11:56.258 --> 11:57.498
Or at least part of it.

11:57.634 --> 11:58.965
Okay, right. I know.

11:59.595 --> 12:00.801
Um...

12:01.054 --> 12:02.260
So we'll pick back up on Monday?

12:02.973 --> 12:03.962
Lundi Gras?

12:04.391 --> 12:05.426
I mean Wednesday.

12:05.517 --> 12:06.848
Leave a day for hangovers.

12:07.853 --> 12:08.888
Thursday it is.

12:08.979 --> 12:10.515
-Yeah, next Thursday it is.
-Cool.

12:10.606 --> 12:12.312
Thank you, guys. I'll see you.

12:22.367 --> 12:24.073
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

12:26.830 --> 12:29.037
(HAMMERING)

12:30.918 --> 12:33.284
You're a little overdressed, son.

12:33.378 --> 12:36.211
Just got back from a memorial service.

12:36.298 --> 12:40.837
Shouldn't you be in some boots and a
10-gallon cowboy hat or something?

12:40.928 --> 12:42.668
(CHUCKLES) When in Rome...

12:42.763 --> 12:46.301
But you're right, I'm back there for real,

12:46.391 --> 12:48.473
which means I'm not
gonna have to put up with your nonsense.

12:48.560 --> 12:49.845
(SCOFFS)

12:49.937 --> 12:52.519
Look, the contracts
we still have, you keep with my blessing.

12:53.065 --> 12:54.430
Maybe throw me five or 10 points

12:54.524 --> 12:55.809
for having brought you to the mountaintop,

12:55.901 --> 12:57.266
or whatever you think is right.

12:57.361 --> 13:00.694
But from here on out,
it's you on the New Orleans demo and rehab.

13:01.365 --> 13:02.855
Fair enough?

13:03.033 --> 13:04.523
More than fair. For me, anyway.

13:05.035 --> 13:07.993
Boy, them people in Galveston don't know
what hit 'em yet, do they?

13:08.080 --> 13:09.490
Hurricane Ike? They know.

13:09.581 --> 13:11.617
Shit. Hurricane Nelson.

13:11.708 --> 13:12.914
(LAUGHING)

13:18.924 --> 13:21.791
Hey, ain't I seen you
at the Sunday Second lines?

13:23.261 --> 13:24.512
Not lately, though.

13:24.596 --> 13:27.338
You just missed CTC a couple of weeks ago.

13:27.891 --> 13:28.926
You're breaking my heart.

13:29.559 --> 13:31.720
They don't do no Second Line
at your college, huh?

13:32.771 --> 13:34.307
I heard that.

13:34.398 --> 13:35.808
-Here you go, baby.
-Keep it.

13:35.899 --> 13:38.891
Sunday after next,
get yourself a hot sausage po-boy and a Bud

13:38.986 --> 13:39.975
and think of me, okay?

13:40.070 --> 13:41.776
I'll do that, miss. I'll do that.

13:41.863 --> 13:42.943
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

13:44.241 --> 13:46.027
TERRY: When we get in that room...

13:46.159 --> 13:47.899
TONI: You'll have to really
watch yourself, all right?

13:47.995 --> 13:51.908
Yeah, once we're in there,
I'm just gonna get to tell the whole story.

13:51.999 --> 13:53.330
Right?

13:53.417 --> 13:54.998
-And they're gonna hear it...
-Well, I know...

13:55.085 --> 13:56.746
-Hey, Mama!
-Sweetie!

13:56.837 --> 13:58.418
Hey, you!

13:58.588 --> 14:00.203
What on earth? Oh, my God.

14:01.675 --> 14:02.915
Now wait a minute.

14:03.010 --> 14:05.296
Don't you have
an anthropology midterm on Monday?

14:05.387 --> 14:06.502
What are you doing home?

14:06.596 --> 14:08.678
I got the TA to test me early.

14:08.765 --> 14:11.142
I told them I had to be back
for a religious observance.

14:11.226 --> 14:12.306
(LAUGHING)

14:12.436 --> 14:13.551
Well, it's true.

14:13.645 --> 14:14.760
So Mardi Gras is on!

14:14.896 --> 14:16.022
(CHEERS)

14:16.106 --> 14:18.062
What's for dinner?

14:18.191 --> 14:20.102
We ate, but I will fix you something right...

14:20.193 --> 14:21.603
No problem. I'll raid the fridge.

14:22.070 --> 14:25.562
It's all better
than the dining hall, I promise you.

14:32.122 --> 14:35.535
What if he just doesn't ask
about the false report?

14:35.625 --> 14:37.752
Just lets it go?

14:38.837 --> 14:40.873
He can't.

14:45.385 --> 14:46.591
(EXHALES)

14:50.307 --> 14:52.548
Okay, what about the front room?

14:52.642 --> 14:53.802
That's our bedroom.

14:53.977 --> 14:55.092
Honore's room?

14:55.187 --> 14:57.098
-Where she gonna sleep?
-With us.

14:59.816 --> 15:00.805
Okay.

15:02.360 --> 15:03.736
It's not forever, right?

15:03.820 --> 15:06.402
Oh, no, no, no, baby.

15:08.992 --> 15:11.574
Do you good to spend
some time with at least two of your sons.

15:11.661 --> 15:13.526
Oh, snap.

15:13.622 --> 15:16.159
Give 'em the front room.
We'll move our bed into Honore's room.

15:17.793 --> 15:19.203
What, they gonna sleep on the floor?

15:19.294 --> 15:20.534
You'll figure it out.

15:22.714 --> 15:25.251
Birds...

15:25.342 --> 15:27.128
(CROWD CHEERING)

15:27.677 --> 15:29.338
SINGER: They fly away

15:30.639 --> 15:31.924
Oh, the birds

15:32.015 --> 15:33.004
Hey!

15:33.183 --> 15:34.673
They fly away

15:34.935 --> 15:36.095
Hey!

15:36.728 --> 15:38.810
Told you I'd make it.

15:39.689 --> 15:41.190
SINGER: You ready?

15:41.483 --> 15:43.519
(VOCALIZING)

15:46.822 --> 15:48.608
(CROWD CHEERING)

15:52.410 --> 15:54.116
How's Yale, Miss Ivy?

15:54.204 --> 15:56.911
You know what they say,
toughest thing is getting in.

15:57.207 --> 15:59.493
(PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC)

15:59.918 --> 16:01.909
(CROWD CHEERING)

16:03.004 --> 16:05.461
(VOCALIZING)

16:26.361 --> 16:28.568
Could it be

16:28.655 --> 16:31.692
That we are fallin'

16:31.908 --> 16:36.618
Like rain falls on the ground?

16:37.747 --> 16:43.583
Tonight I hear the city callin'

16:43.670 --> 16:47.663
The people and the sound...

16:49.593 --> 16:52.050
BAILIFF: Do you solemnly swear and affirm

16:52.137 --> 16:54.753
to tell the truth, the whole truth,

16:54.890 --> 16:57.472
and nothing but the truth, so help you God?

16:57.559 --> 16:59.140
I do.

17:01.438 --> 17:02.769
Have a seat, Lieutenant.

17:09.196 --> 17:10.936
To begin today's session of the Grand Jury

17:11.114 --> 17:12.900
for the Eastern District of Louisiana...

17:13.200 --> 17:15.191
(TRUMPET PLAYING)

17:50.278 --> 17:52.815
(LET THE GOOD TIMES ROLL
PLAYING ON STEREO)

19:06.938 --> 19:08.269
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

19:08.565 --> 19:11.682
You think your mama
and me are gonna lug this mess up in there?

19:11.776 --> 19:12.765
Is that what you think?

19:15.196 --> 19:16.356
Hmm?

19:19.326 --> 19:20.862
You've been spoiling 'em, I see.

19:21.703 --> 19:24.615
Shit is over under my roof, baby.

19:27.417 --> 19:28.907
Come on.

19:53.610 --> 19:54.599
Papers.

19:54.694 --> 19:55.854
I just take your forms and your badge.

19:55.945 --> 19:57.856
The rest of this shit
goes to the gun range and the academy.

19:57.947 --> 19:59.608
Deal with it. I'm out.

20:15.507 --> 20:17.122
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

20:22.305 --> 20:23.465
Davis, what the fuck?

20:23.640 --> 20:24.846
Gentlemen.

20:24.933 --> 20:26.389
Dude, is that a costume?

20:29.979 --> 20:31.810
Seriously, Davis.

20:31.898 --> 20:34.560
Krewe d'Etat
comes down the Avenue in an hour, brah.

20:34.651 --> 20:36.187
Let's go hail the new dictator.

20:37.987 --> 20:39.443
Got a job.

20:40.448 --> 20:41.403
What?

20:41.491 --> 20:42.822
(BOTH LAUGH IN DISBELIEF)

20:42.909 --> 20:44.945
Are you kidding?

20:45.036 --> 20:46.492
What?

20:49.707 --> 20:51.038
RANDALL: Anything we can do yet?

20:51.126 --> 20:55.745
Yeah. I'm supposed
to have 16 of these octagonal suckers,

20:55.839 --> 20:56.828
-but I only got 15,
-(PHONE RINGING)

20:56.923 --> 20:58.629
so one of them
must have rolled under somewhere.

