(LAUGHS)

37:13.857 --> 37:16.769
Everybody here, hey

37:17.069 --> 37:19.310
Clean it up, all the paper and trash

37:19.405 --> 37:21.316
Get that stuff outta here

37:21.657 --> 37:23.989
Clean up after Mardi Gras

37:24.201 --> 37:26.408
I know what I know, Annie.

37:26.495 --> 37:27.985
I've learned what I've learned.

37:28.163 --> 37:29.664
You can't ask me to unlearn it.

37:32.084 --> 37:36.043
Okay. Well, I've learned a few things, too.

37:37.339 --> 37:39.000
Like what?

37:39.842 --> 37:43.585
Like you can only bend so far

37:43.679 --> 37:47.342
before everything
you're doing doesn't matter anymore

37:48.267 --> 37:50.633
until you've lost the point.

37:50.727 --> 37:52.183
But I bent for you.

37:52.271 --> 37:53.886
Is this about Bayou Cadillac?

37:53.981 --> 37:55.562
No, Marvin. Listen to me.

37:55.649 --> 37:58.436
I gave up the band, and I followed you here.

37:58.527 --> 38:01.485
And I'm willing to try and make
music the way you think I should.

38:01.905 --> 38:04.442
Maybe my band wasn't pretty enough.

38:04.575 --> 38:07.112
Maybe they sounded a little too Louisiana.

38:07.202 --> 38:08.783
Maybe we had a ceiling because of that.

38:08.871 --> 38:12.363
And maybe it's worth
trying something a little more mainstream

38:12.458 --> 38:15.120
and tarting it up some. We'll see.

38:15.919 --> 38:18.831
But it has to be
my fucking music that I'm making.

38:18.922 --> 38:21.379
I mean, if it isn't music that I love,

38:21.550 --> 38:24.041
that I make, that I wanna play,

38:25.053 --> 38:26.793
what the fuck is the point?

38:28.557 --> 38:29.672
I'm serious.

38:29.808 --> 38:30.888
I see that.

38:33.061 --> 38:37.896
