I don't wanna start nothing I can't finish.

42:50.193 --> 42:51.808
I can't promise I'm gonna be here next year.

42:51.903 --> 42:53.814
Or the year after that.

42:55.031 --> 42:56.407
My daddy's legacy with the Guardians,

42:56.533 --> 42:57.864
that's for you to carry, not me.

42:58.410 --> 43:01.152
I carry him in my own way.

43:01.455 --> 43:04.913
Me Big Chief I got my tribe

43:05.000 --> 43:08.413
Got my squaw right by my side

43:08.503 --> 43:11.791
My flag boyjust went by

43:11.882 --> 43:15.591
My flag boy is full of pride

43:15.677 --> 43:19.135
My whole tribe is having fun

43:19.222 --> 43:22.464
We're gonna dance till the morning come

43:23.226 --> 43:24.932
(WHISTLING)

43:26.688 --> 43:28.019
(CAMERA CLICKING)

43:28.106 --> 43:30.097
PHOTOGRAPHER: All right, very nice.

43:30.192 --> 43:31.648
(CLICKING CONTINUES)

43:32.527 --> 43:34.904
You know what?
Go ahead and dance around for me.

43:34.988 --> 43:36.353
Okay.

43:36.448 --> 43:37.563
(LAUGHS)

43:39.367 --> 43:41.744
(GIGGLING) Hard to dance in these.

43:41.828 --> 43:43.659
It's all right. Just relax. Just relax.

43:44.206 --> 43:45.571
Now give me a little twirl.

43:45.665 --> 43:46.700
Okay.

43:46.875 --> 43:47.910
A twirl... There you go. There you go.

43:48.001 --> 43:51.664
Very nice, very nice.
And hold it right there. Hold it right there.

43:51.755 --> 43:55.168
Chin up. Give me more.
More in the eyes. Intense.

43:55.258 --> 43:57.715
That's pretty. Real pretty.

43:58.053 --> 44:00.044
-(DRUMS PLAYING)
-MAN: Coochie ma!

44:02.224 --> 44:04.260
Coochie ma!

44:04.351 --> 44:06.307
(GUARDIANS SHOUTING)

44:08.021 --> 44:10.558
MAN: A crowd
every morning, 'cause here they come

44:10.649 --> 44:12.355
ALL: Guardians, here they come

44:12.442 --> 44:14.774
Put your name on the screen, gonna carry on

44:14.861 --> 44:16.522
Guardians, here they come

44:16.613 --> 44:19.070
Hey, Mardi Gras mornin' the whole gang know

44:19.157 --> 44:20.738
Guardians, here they come

44:20.826 --> 44:23.158
We gonna arrange
this number for Chief Lambreaux

44:23.245 --> 44:24.325
Guardians, here they come

44:24.412 --> 44:25.447
(YELLING)

44:25.539 --> 44:27.450
Hey, Mardi Gras day and Saint Joe night

44:27.541 --> 44:29.657
Guardians, here they come

44:29.751 --> 44:31.662
We're pouring
like diamonds, shining like light

44:31.753 --> 44:33.459
Guardians, here they come

44:33.547 --> 44:36.084
I'm gonna bring that thing,
has the light of the moon

44:36.174 --> 44:37.835
Guardians, here they come

44:37.926 --> 44:40.258
I've been
a Big Chief comin', killed Daniel Boone

44:40.387 --> 44:44.471
Coochie ma! I'm the pretty gang flag.

44:44.683 --> 44:46.173
ALL: Guardians, here they come

44:46.268 --> 44:48.759
Oh, Lord have mercy, Chief got mad

44:48.854 --> 44:50.515
Guardians, here they come

44:50.605 --> 44:52.937
His spy don't worry, his flag don't kneel

44:53.024 --> 44:54.764
Guardians, here they come

44:54.860 --> 44:57.272
Got a Big Chief comin' with a heart of steel

44:57.362 --> 44:59.023
Guardians, here they come

44:59.114 --> 45:01.571
His spy boy don't worry, your Chief on fire

45:01.658 --> 45:03.273
Guardians, here they come

45:03.368 --> 45:05.859
They be the Indian ruler on Mardi Gras

45:05.954 --> 45:07.785
Guardians, here they come

45:07.873 --> 45:09.989
Just, uh, let 'em come

45:10.083 --> 45:11.619
Guardians, here they come

45:11.710 --> 45:14.167
I sayjust, uh, let 'em come

45:16.131 --> 45:19.498
All righty. You ready for some sleeve photos?

45:19.593 --> 45:21.174
Full band with Annie in front.

45:21.261 --> 45:22.751
What do you think?

45:22.888 --> 45:24.378
Give mejust a minute.

45:24.472 --> 45:26.383
-Hey.
-Wow, look at you.

45:26.474 --> 45:27.463
(GIGGLING)

45:27.642 --> 45:28.631
Just another Tuesday, huh?

45:28.727 --> 45:29.887
What do you mean?

45:30.020 --> 45:31.135
I thought you were from New Orleans.

45:31.229 --> 45:32.389
It's Mardi Gras today, right?

45:32.480 --> 45:33.606
PHOTOGRAPHER: Guys,
let's get you in the center.

45:33.690 --> 45:34.805
It's Mardi Gras?

45:34.900 --> 45:36.436
-Right over here.
-Yeah.

45:36.526 --> 45:37.811
(GASPS)

45:39.696 --> 45:42.438
It's all right. They'll do it next year.

45:42.824 --> 45:44.485
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

45:46.620 --> 45:47.735
You gonna come with, right?

45:47.829 --> 45:49.444
Sure. I haven't seen a truck parade

45:49.581 --> 45:51.162
since my nephew rode before the storm.

45:51.249 --> 45:52.830
I know he's excited about it.

45:53.793 --> 45:55.249
I got to find the ladies' room.

45:55.337 --> 45:57.123
Can't find no place to pee on Mardi Gras Day.

45:57.213 --> 45:59.750
True dat. Watch the baby.

46:02.052 --> 46:04.213
Hey, boo-boo.

46:04.304 --> 46:08.263
Hey, let me hear you say,
"Throw me something, mister."

46:08.350 --> 46:10.306
-Throw me something, mister.
-Yeah!

46:10.393 --> 46:12.509
Hey, very good.

46:12.896 --> 46:14.011
(LAUGHS)

46:15.523 --> 46:16.774
Antoine?

46:16.858 --> 46:18.769
-Hey.
-Hey.

46:20.654 --> 46:21.939
-How you doing?
-How you doing?

46:22.030 --> 46:23.190
Happy Mardi Gras.

46:23.365 --> 46:24.571
Happy Mardi Gras.

46:24.658 --> 46:25.818
Nice to see you.

46:25.951 --> 46:27.111
Nice to see you, too.

46:27.202 --> 46:29.944
Yeah, I haven't seen you since...

46:30.038 --> 46:31.448
-Since last Mardi Gras.
-Last Mardi Gras.

46:31.539 --> 46:33.120
Right, right.

46:33.208 --> 46:35.699
So, you gonna join us later?

46:37.295 --> 46:40.207
Well, I'd like to, yeah.

46:40.298 --> 46:44.962
But I don't think I can this year.

46:45.053 --> 46:46.338
Well, if you change your mind,

46:46.429 --> 46:48.761
we'll be at
Crescent City Steak House around 6:00.

46:48.848 --> 46:50.008
-Around 6:00?
-6:00.

46:50.100 --> 46:51.510
All right.

46:51.601 --> 46:52.636
Happy Mardi Gras.

46:52.769 --> 46:53.804
Good to see you.

46:53.895 --> 46:55.726
-Nice to see you.
-Yeah.

46:55.814 --> 46:57.270
6:00.

47:00.443 --> 47:05.278
Hey, hey, hey. Look,
text me. You know, as soon as you get there.

47:05.365 --> 47:07.526
Just in case.

47:09.494 --> 47:11.485
You burning the meat.

47:14.249 --> 47:16.160
I don't want none.

47:16.251 --> 47:17.536
You want some?

47:17.669 --> 47:18.909
No, I don't want none.

47:19.004 --> 47:20.039
What?

47:22.007 --> 47:24.840
So, if I am to understand you correctly,

47:24.926 --> 47:29.886
you and your entire cohort
mark this day annually

47:29.973 --> 47:34.262
by dressing
as local rodentia and parading en masse

47:34.352 --> 47:36.889
down this public thoroughfare?

47:36.980 --> 47:38.265
We're a krewe.

47:38.440 --> 47:39.725
Interesting.

47:39.816 --> 47:44.560
And are you subject
to any form of sociopolitical leadership?

47:44.654 --> 47:45.985
We have a king every year.

47:46.072 --> 47:48.734
We're the Mystic
Krewe of Nutria. (IMITATES SQUIRREL)

47:48.825 --> 47:51.487
"The Mystic Krewe of Nutria."

47:51.578 --> 47:52.613
Is he for real?

47:56.249 --> 47:57.409
Lighten up, Francis.

47:57.500 --> 47:59.240
-Oh. Thank you.
-(LAUGHING)

47:59.335 --> 48:00.461
Happy Mardi Gras.

48:00.587 --> 48:01.702
Hey, look, Saint Anne's is coming through.

48:01.796 --> 48:03.081
-Come on.
-You know...

48:03.173 --> 48:04.458
Let's go to the river.

48:04.632 --> 48:05.883
Frankly, all of this,

48:05.967 --> 48:08.333
while colorful
and provocative, makes little sense.

48:08.428 --> 48:11.841
To assert membership
in a quasi-religious cohort

48:11.931 --> 48:14.638
that worships
a small swamp mammal of obscure origin

48:14.726 --> 48:16.637
is culturally marginal at best.

48:17.228 --> 48:18.729
(ALL CHEERING)

48:31.242 --> 48:33.654
ANTOINE: Antoine and Alcide, Alcide!

48:33.912 --> 48:36.995
Alcide, Alcide, Alcide!

48:37.082 --> 48:39.448
Hey! Hey!

48:39.542 --> 48:40.657
Come on! Come on!

48:43.505 --> 48:46.042
Alcide, Alcide! Wait, wait!

48:46.132 --> 48:49.499
Alcide! Alcide! Hey!

48:50.345 --> 48:52.176
(PLAYING JAZZ MUSIC)

48:57.060 --> 48:58.971
What?

48:59.104 --> 49:00.935
I just don't get what's eating you.

49:01.022 --> 49:03.809
Turning 40? Who cares?

49:03.900 --> 49:06.061
I'm just trying to make a point.

49:06.152 --> 49:10.771
How many Mardi Gras does one man
have? How many does he need?

49:10.865 --> 49:13.402
At what point do you look around,

49:13.493 --> 49:16.906
and suddenly,
you're the old fart on the dance floor?

49:16.996 --> 49:19.533
And so this, this is your approximation

49:19.666 --> 49:22.157
of a grown-up, Davis? Really? Seriously?

49:22.252 --> 49:26.461
My father wears
a jacket and tie every day of his life.

49:26.548 --> 49:27.708
You want to be your father?

49:27.882 --> 49:29.088
God, no.

49:29.175 --> 49:34.135
But at some point,
I imagine myself being some version of him.

49:34.222 --> 49:36.304
Maybe a husband

49:36.391 --> 49:40.475
with a cat, and a dog,
and a lawn, lawn furniture.

49:40.562 --> 49:42.268
It's not gonna happen, my friend.

49:42.355 --> 49:45.643
You are DJ Davis, the one and only.

49:45.733 --> 49:48.315
I gotta get rid of that guy.

49:48.403 --> 49:50.394
Fucker's holding me back.

49:53.116 --> 49:54.902
-(HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING)
-(CROWD CHEERING)

50:13.344 --> 50:15.380
There he is! There he is! Right there.

50:18.183 --> 50:21.095
Hey! Hey!

50:38.161 --> 50:39.526
(GUNFIRE)

50:39.621 --> 50:40.861
MAN 1: They're shooting! They're shooting!

50:40.955 --> 50:42.695
Somebody's motherfuckin' shooting, man!

50:42.790 --> 50:44.166
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

50:44.250 --> 50:46.332
MAN 2: Shit, they're shooting. Fuck that, man.

50:46.419 --> 50:47.955
MAN 3: Stay down!

50:48.087 --> 50:49.543
You see who it was?

50:49.631 --> 50:50.962
(MEN SHOUTING)

51:00.975 --> 51:02.226
(SCREAMING)

51:09.400 --> 51:11.391
Somebody help me!

51:12.987 --> 51:13.976
Call for help!

51:16.532 --> 51:18.363
(PEOPLE CLAMORING)

51:38.179 --> 51:39.965
(BAND PLAYING JAZZ MUSIC)

52:11.671 --> 52:13.036
(MUSIC STOPS)

52:13.631 --> 52:15.667
(CROWD CHEERING)

52:21.764 --> 52:23.720
You ran the good race, little brother.

52:37.697 --> 52:39.028
Davis, what the fuck?

52:40.908 --> 52:42.239
MAN 1: Look at this goof.

52:42.410 --> 52:43.650
I'm baptizing myself.

52:43.745 --> 52:45.576
Please get out of the river.

52:46.497 --> 52:47.828
That's stupid.

52:47.957 --> 52:49.288
I'm laying down my burden.

52:49.375 --> 52:50.785
MAN 2: What are you dressed as?

52:50.877 --> 52:54.085
The bright Mississippi, wash me clean.

52:56.758 --> 52:58.339
MAN 3: There you go.

52:58.718 --> 53:01.505
MAN 4: We normally don't
put them into the river until they're ashes.

53:01.596 --> 53:03.177
It's kind of a rule, Davis.

53:03.264 --> 53:04.765
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

53:04.849 --> 53:05.929
Whoa!

53:07.310 --> 53:12.100
I'm born again, baptized in this muddy water!

53:12.190 --> 53:15.648
I am no longer DJ Davis.

53:15.735 --> 53:17.441
lam

53:17.987 --> 53:19.488
Mr. McAlary!

53:20.031 --> 53:21.316
(ALL CHEERING)

53:25.828 --> 53:27.944
(DAVIS GROANING)

53:33.795 --> 53:34.830
Be careful.

53:40.218 --> 53:41.924
DJ Davis is dead.

53:42.637 --> 53:44.298
-I don't think so.
-No.

53:44.972 --> 53:47.509
I am Mr. McAlary.

53:47.600 --> 53:51.138
Like my father and his father before him.

53:51.229 --> 53:53.641
I don't think your father ever walked

53:53.815 --> 53:56.181
in the Mississippi River in his best suit.

53:57.235 --> 54:00.272
No. Not sober, anyway.

54:05.576 --> 54:08.488
They should have been here by now.

54:09.831 --> 54:12.072
By the way, I want to thank you

54:12.208 --> 54:14.494
for everything you've done for the boys.

54:15.837 --> 54:18.044
And them coming to live here now,

54:18.172 --> 54:20.424
that wasn't easy for you, I know.

54:20.508 --> 54:22.464
It's the right thing.

54:24.011 --> 54:27.503
Well, you know what they say.
Takes a village, right?

54:29.600 --> 54:34.435
You need one
fucked-up musician, a tax-paying dentist...

54:34.522 --> 54:36.558
And your damn-near-bipolar,

54:36.649 --> 54:39.015
what-does-she-want-today,
crazy-ass bar owner.

54:39.110 --> 54:40.850
(BOTH LAUGHING)

54:41.154 --> 54:42.439
That's some woman, ain't she?

54:42.572 --> 54:43.857
Yeah, she is.

54:52.540 --> 54:54.121
Guys, there's food inside,

54:54.208 --> 54:56.699
and your sister's waiting to see you.

54:58.504 --> 55:00.711
We're okay, Dad.

55:03.759 --> 55:04.794
How are they?

55:05.887 --> 55:08.629
It was scary, but they're okay.

55:08.723 --> 55:10.964
News said seven wounded.

55:11.058 --> 55:12.559
It was awful.

55:13.728 --> 55:16.344
I'm gonna go check in on the boys.

55:22.195 --> 55:23.935
Thank God you're all okay.

55:24.405 --> 55:26.316
By the grace of God.

55:31.162 --> 55:32.402
(SOBBING)

55:34.248 --> 55:35.909
It's okay.

55:37.001 --> 55:39.083
(UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING)

56:01.442 --> 56:06.061
Man, my shoes feel
like science projects. I got...

56:06.155 --> 56:07.315
There's something crawling in there.

56:07.448 --> 56:08.654
That serves you right.

56:10.785 --> 56:13.401
To time and its passing.

56:13.496 --> 56:14.906
(CLINKING)

56:21.921 --> 56:23.252
I love you.

56:26.467 --> 56:27.832
Of course you do, Davis.

56:30.805 --> 56:31.794
Dance.

56:33.140 --> 56:34.129
All right.

58:15.660 --> 58:20.245
This is for the civil docket.
Robert Gilday versus Sheriff Gusman et al.

58:30.800 --> 58:32.131
NELSON: Who cares that
a couple of politically

58:32.259 --> 58:33.635
connected people are in on the deal?

58:33.719 --> 58:35.004
Never happens othenNise.

58:35.096 --> 58:36.085
Bernardo Wade, man.

58:36.263 --> 58:37.252
And who the hell's that?

58:37.348 --> 58:39.179
He's Nagin's personal photographer.

58:39.266 --> 58:41.348
We have him in our proposal
as the compliance officer.

58:41.435 --> 58:42.845
Whatever that means.

58:42.978 --> 58:44.354
It means bagman for all I care.

58:44.438 --> 58:46.474
Look, you can't get a deal through City Hall

58:46.565 --> 58:48.601
without Ray Nagin
or his people laying in the cut somewhere.

58:48.693 --> 58:49.682
So what?

58:49.777 --> 58:52.314
It's still a project
that this city should want regardless.

58:52.405 --> 58:53.360
The Times-Pic is still angry

58:53.447 --> 58:56.280
about the party Bernardo
threw for Nagin last year, remember?

58:56.367 --> 58:58.574
Having him in this deal was a red flag.

58:58.661 --> 59:00.151
Oh, Christ's sakes, it's New Orleans.

59:00.246 --> 59:02.362
There's always
a Bernardo Wade in the mix somewhere.

59:02.456 --> 59:04.196
You telling me he stops this project?

59:04.291 --> 59:05.622
It's dead.

59:05.710 --> 59:08.543
What we just saw up
there was a sharpening of the knives.

59:08.629 --> 59:11.416
I busted my ass
for three years to get this thing built.

59:11.507 --> 59:14.044
I pissed off the Mayor.
I pissed off the Lieutenant Governor.

59:14.135 --> 59:16.672
I pissed off
everyone else down the line along the way,

59:16.762 --> 59:19.845
but who cares if
the thing gets built? Who cares?

59:19.932 --> 59:21.888
We'd have a national venue
for New Orleans music.

59:21.976 --> 59:23.887
But now?

59:23.978 --> 59:27.971
Go play some trumpet,
kiddo. You'll feel better in the morning.

59:31.402 --> 59:33.142
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

59:43.914 --> 59:45.415
Hey, hey, how are you?

59:47.334 --> 59:49.120
Whoa, what's eating you?

59:49.211 --> 59:50.246
You sued me, Toni.

59:51.464 --> 59:54.422
Come on, honey.
I sue everybody. You know that.

59:58.512 --> 59:59.922
How's the bread pudding, hmm?

1:00:03.350 --> 1:00:05.056
There you go.

1:00:06.270 --> 1:00:08.181
(BOTH LAUGHING)

1:00:09.356 --> 1:00:11.017
I ever tell you my Harry Lee story?

1:00:11.150 --> 1:00:12.765
About a million times.

1:00:12.860 --> 1:00:14.270
No, I don't think I ever did.

1:00:14.361 --> 1:00:15.976
And you can deliver this to me?

1:00:16.071 --> 1:00:18.107
I can. I absolutely guarantee it.

1:00:18.199 --> 1:00:20.781
I'm tight with everyone
who's in on the decision.

1:00:20.868 --> 1:00:24.986
I can promise you
that if that Jazz Center gets built,

1:00:25.080 --> 1:00:27.287
a Feeny restaurant
will be a part of it. You have my word.

1:00:30.211 --> 1:00:31.667
l have one thing to ask in return.

1:00:33.088 --> 1:00:34.339
Name it.

1:00:34.423 --> 1:00:37.711
I had a long
talk with Woodrow. He's chomping at the bit.

1:00:37.802 --> 1:00:40.043
Can't wait till I get back up there.

1:00:40.137 --> 1:00:42.002
I mean, it makes sense
for me to be based in New York.

1:00:42.097 --> 1:00:43.962
There's no place down here
for me to play my music.

1:00:44.058 --> 1:00:46.595
Are we gonna find a place in Manhattan?

1:00:46.685 --> 1:00:50.052
I'm thinking Brooklyn.
More bang for your buck.

1:00:50.564 --> 1:00:52.395
We'll need two bedrooms.

1:00:54.985 --> 1:00:57.818
I want to have the baby here, Del.

1:00:57.905 --> 1:00:58.985
I figured.

1:00:59.073 --> 1:01:01.314
Your mama, your doctor.

1:01:08.374 --> 1:01:13.243
I promised my daddy
we'd raise him or her up in the tradition.

1:01:16.006 --> 1:01:19.999
So, we keep a foot in both places, right?

1:01:20.803 --> 1:01:22.043
Always.

1:01:28.352 --> 1:01:30.889
But how? He hates me so much.

1:01:30.980 --> 1:01:33.687
He likes money more.

1:01:33.774 --> 1:01:35.435
What'd you give him?

1:01:35.609 --> 1:01:37.270
100% of nothing.

1:01:40.614 --> 1:01:41.729
You know something?

1:01:41.824 --> 1:01:45.658
I spent time in this town, made a lot of money.

1:01:45.744 --> 1:01:48.406
And a friend of mine, a cousin, actually,

1:01:48.539 --> 1:01:51.155
once asked me if I ever built anything,

1:01:51.250 --> 1:01:55.118
or if anything ever got fixed
for all that I got paid.

1:01:58.340 --> 1:01:59.750
When you put your sign up,

1:01:59.842 --> 1:02:01.503
take a little penknife, carve my initials

1:02:01.635 --> 1:02:03.296
in the bottom of that sucker, okay?

1:02:04.680 --> 1:02:06.716
I'll do more than that.

1:02:06.807 --> 1:02:09.219
You got this corner table
any time you want it, gratis.

1:02:09.310 --> 1:02:13.644
Oh, no, darling,
I pay for my meals. And I tip excessively.

1:02:13.731 --> 1:02:15.062
Never worry the little stuff.

1:02:17.526 --> 1:02:18.732
Mmm.

1:02:19.820 --> 1:02:21.321
AII right. (SIGHS)

1:02:22.239 --> 1:02:24.776
Gotta go. I'm in the wrong town.

1:02:24.867 --> 1:02:26.573
TOBY: Godzilla versus King Kong.

1:02:26.660 --> 1:02:29.151
It's a flawed analogy, Davis.

1:02:31.248 --> 1:02:34.490
If Fess is M.L.K.,

1:02:34.585 --> 1:02:36.576
Booker is Gandhi.

1:02:36.670 --> 1:02:37.830
(LAUGHING)

1:02:39.465 --> 1:02:43.925
So the Mahatma
is the Civil Rights equivalent of Godzilla.

1:02:44.011 --> 1:02:45.797
Indeed.

1:02:45.930 --> 1:02:47.636
Okay, Godzilla versus M.L.K.

1:02:47.723 --> 1:02:49.088
-Who wins?
-Wait, wait, wait, wait.

1:02:49.642 --> 1:02:50.757
That's a lyric.

1:02:50.851 --> 1:02:52.011
No! That's a song!

1:02:52.144 --> 1:02:53.259
Oh, God, here we go.

1:02:53.354 --> 1:02:56.437
Shit! That's a concept album.

1:02:57.608 --> 1:02:59.690
Right? Right?

1:03:00.319 --> 1:03:01.354
What the fuck did I just say?

1:03:01.445 --> 1:03:04.687
BOTH: Godzilla versus M.L.K.

1:03:05.574 --> 1:03:07.565
(PLAYING COUNTRY MUSIC)

1:03:19.213 --> 1:03:21.579
(CROWD CHEERING)

1:03:23.550 --> 1:03:28.260
Goin' to the place where I was born

1:03:29.890 --> 1:03:35.726
Long before this world was my home

1:03:36.897 --> 1:03:39.138
I gotta go, gotta go

1:03:39.233 --> 1:03:42.350
But I don't know when

1:03:43.487 --> 1:03:49.198
Oh, come with me, oh, if you can

1:03:50.411 --> 1:03:55.701
Oh, come with me, oh, if you can

1:04:03.757 --> 1:04:05.042
(SONG ENDS)

1:04:05.134 --> 1:04:06.840
(CROWD CHEERING)

1:04:11.515 --> 1:04:13.927
Thank you so much, you guys. Thank you.

1:04:14.018 --> 1:04:16.009
That one will be on our new record,

1:04:16.145 --> 1:04:18.101
which will be out
this summer, we hope. (GIGGLES)

1:04:20.733 --> 1:04:24.396
You know what? It's so good
to be back in New Orleans after so long.

1:04:24.486 --> 1:04:28.695
I have so many friends down here that I miss,

1:04:28.782 --> 1:04:30.738
and actually, I see one of them right now.

1:04:31.827 --> 1:04:33.943
It's my oldest friend here.

1:04:34.038 --> 1:04:38.532
He's the one who dragged me to New
Orleans and made me love the place.

1:04:40.794 --> 1:04:43.456
This one is for him.

1:04:43.547 --> 1:04:45.708
All right, you Nashville hotshots,

1:04:45.799 --> 1:04:48.882
every busker down here
can play this one in, like, five different keys.

1:04:48.969 --> 1:04:50.960
So we can do this.

1:04:51.555 --> 1:04:52.840
(ANNIE CLEARS THROAT)

1:04:53.474 --> 1:04:55.089
Okay.

1:04:57.811 --> 1:04:59.267
(PLAYING CARELESS LOVE)

1:05:01.023 --> 1:05:03.639
(APPLAUSE)

1:05:06.320 --> 1:05:09.733
Love, oh, love

1:05:09.823 --> 1:05:12.155
Oh, careless love

1:05:12.242 --> 1:05:14.494
(APPLAUSE)

1:05:14.578 --> 1:05:18.742
You fly through my head

1:05:18.832 --> 1:05:21.323
Like wine

1:05:22.753 --> 1:05:26.621
You wrecked the life

1:05:26.715 --> 1:05:30.674
Of many poor girls

1:05:31.512 --> 1:05:35.596
And you let me spoil

1:05:35.682 --> 1:05:38.344
This life of mine

1:05:40.187 --> 1:05:43.679
ALL: Love, oh, love

1:05:43.774 --> 1:05:46.561
Oh, careless love

1:05:50.155 --> 1:05:54.819
In your clutches of desire

1:05:56.870 --> 1:06:00.613
You made me break

1:06:00.707 --> 1:06:05.326
A many true vow

1:06:05.420 --> 1:06:09.754
Then you set my very soul

1:06:09.842 --> 1:06:12.208
On fire

1:06:13.262 --> 1:06:17.551
This is DJ Davis on WWOZ,
the world's greatest radio station.

1:06:17.641 --> 1:06:21.384
That was the late,
great Earl King with Ain't No City.

1:06:22.479 --> 1:06:25.767
Do you have your
Brass Passes yet? Jazz Fest is coming,

1:06:25.858 --> 1:06:29.771
and we do not want
to get caught naked and bereft, now, do we?

1:06:31.029 --> 1:06:32.485
DARNELL: Davis.

1:06:32.614 --> 1:06:34.115
MAN ON HEADPHONES: Attention, listeners...

1:06:34.199 --> 1:06:35.234
Yes, Darnell?

1:06:35.325 --> 1:06:36.940
I just wanted to tell you that your shows

1:06:37.077 --> 1:06:38.738
the last few weeks have been really good.

1:06:39.288 --> 1:06:40.994
Really tight.

1:06:42.916 --> 1:06:46.374
Your shows, they've been good.

1:06:47.880 --> 1:06:49.336
Why would you say something like that?

1:06:49.423 --> 1:06:51.664
Why would you go there
when you know how much that fucks me up?

1:06:51.758 --> 1:06:57.845
Do you understand the self-loathing involved
when you, the station manager,

1:06:57.931 --> 1:07:01.719
comes in here to
tell me that you enjoy what I'm doing, hmm?

1:07:04.980 --> 1:07:06.311
My mistake.

1:07:07.482 --> 1:07:08.983
Darnell!

1:07:11.653 --> 1:07:14.190
Dude, you're way too easy.

1:07:15.157 --> 1:07:16.567
(LAUGHING)

1:07:26.293 --> 1:07:29.126
MAN ON HEADPHONES:
We hope to see you at the Fest.

1:07:31.465 --> 1:07:33.547
Hey, do you know how sometimes

1:07:33.634 --> 1:07:36.341
you hear a song
that you've heard a million times before,

1:07:36.428 --> 1:07:39.636
and maybe you're even tired of hearing it?

1:07:40.807 --> 1:07:42.138
But this time,

1:07:44.519 --> 1:07:47.727
maybe because of something
you've been through,

1:07:47.814 --> 1:07:52.558
or maybe because of something
you now understand,

1:07:52.653 --> 1:07:54.644
you hear that song again.

1:07:56.156 --> 1:07:59.319
Maybe it's a new version, maybe not.

1:08:00.869 --> 1:08:05.363
But you realize that
there's a fresh world in there to be heard.

1:08:07.376 --> 1:08:08.866
Yeah.

1:08:10.504 --> 1:08:12.165
Me, too.

